# Cypilot Testing Integration

This document bridges Cypilot FEATURE specifications with the BDD test framework (Playwright + playwright-bdd).

## Overview

Every Cypilot FEATURE that modifies UI **MUST** include automated E2E tests. Tests are generated from `FEATURE.md` requirements using `/testing:spec-to-tests`.

## Workflow

```
1. /cypilot-plan
   └─> Creates phased plan from FEATURE spec
   └─> Includes testing phase

2. /cypilot-generate
   └─> Implements feature from FEATURE spec
   └─> Generates BDD tests from FEATURE.md
   └─> Runs tests to verify

3. Tests remain in tests/ and src/mfe_packages/*/tests/
```

## Test Artifacts from FEATURE Spec

For each Cypilot `FEATURE.md`, the following test artifacts are created:

### 1. Feature File
**Location:** `src/mfe_packages/{mfeName}/tests/{screenId}.feature`

**Source:** Actor Flows (Section 2), Definitions of Done (Section 5), Acceptance Criteria (Section 6) from `FEATURE.md`

**Format:**
```gherkin
@feature:{feature-name} @flow:{cpt-hai3-flow-id}
Feature: {Capability Name}

  Scenario: {Scenario Name}
    Given {precondition}
    When {action}
    Then {verification}
```

### 2. Page Object Methods
**Location:** `tests/ui/pages/{screen-id}-page.ts`

**Source:** UI interactions implied by Actor Flows and Acceptance Criteria

**Pattern:** Actions only (`click*`, `get*`, `fill*`)

### 3. Step Definitions
**Location:** `tests/steps/{section}.steps.ts`

**Source:** Gherkin steps from feature file

**Pattern:**
- `When()` → call page object methods
- `Then()` → assertions + verification

### 4. Locators
**Location:** `tests/ui/locators.ts`

**Source:** qa-class attributes from React components (added via `/testing:locators`)

### 5. Fixtures
**Location:** `tests/fixtures/fixtures.ts`

**Source:** Page object registration via `test.extend()`

## Testing Phase Template

When running `/cypilot-generate` for UI features, include this testing phase:

```markdown
## E2E Testing
- [ ] Generate feature file from FEATURE.md
- [ ] Add page object methods to tests/ui/pages/{screen-id}-page.ts
- [ ] Add step definitions to tests/steps/{section}.steps.ts
- [ ] Register page object fixtures in tests/fixtures/fixtures.ts
- [ ] Add qa-class attributes to components (if needed)
- [ ] Run tests: npx bddgen && npx playwright test --project=chromium
```

## FEATURE Requirements → Test Coverage

| FEATURE Section | Test Artifact | Tool |
|-----------------|---------------|------|
| Actor Flows (Section 2) | `@flow:{cpt-id}` tag + Gherkin scenarios | `/testing:spec-to-tests` |
| Definitions of Done (Section 5) | `@dod:{cpt-id}` tag + verification scenarios | `/testing:spec-to-tests` |
| Acceptance Criteria (Section 6) | `@feature:{name}` + `@acceptance` tags | `/testing:spec-to-tests` |
| UI interactions | Page object methods | `/testing:spec-to-tests` |
| Component selectors | Locator constants + qa-class | `/testing:locators` |

## Example: Studio DevTools

### Input: `architecture/features/feature-studio-devtools/FEATURE.md`

**Actor Flow:**
```markdown
### Drag Panel to New Position
- [x] `p1` - **ID**: `cpt-hai3-flow-studio-devtools-drag-panel`
1. [x] - `p1` - Developer presses and holds the panel header - `inst-press-header`
2. [x] - `p1` - Developer drags the panel to a new in-viewport position - `inst-drag-to-position`
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
```markdown
- [x] Studio panel renders as a fixed glassmorphic overlay in development mode
- [x] Panel can be dragged to any in-viewport position
```

### Output: Test Artifacts

**Feature:** `src/mfe_packages/demo-mfe/tests/studio-devtools.feature`
```gherkin
@feature:studio-devtools @acceptance
Scenario: Studio panel renders in development mode
  Given the application is running in development mode
  Then the Studio panel should be visible as a fixed overlay

@feature:studio-devtools @flow:cpt-hai3-flow-studio-devtools-drag-panel
Scenario: Studio panel can be dragged
  Given the Studio panel is visible
  When I drag the panel header to a new position
  Then the panel should move to the new position
```

**Page Object:** `tests/ui/pages/studio-devtools-page.ts`
```typescript
export class StudioDevtoolsPage extends BasePage {
  async dragPanelTo(x: number, y: number): Promise<void> {
    await this.dragElement(STUDIO_DEVTOOLS.PANEL_HEADER, x, y);
  }
}
```

**Step:** `tests/steps/studio-devtools.steps.ts`
```typescript
Then('the Studio panel should be visible as a fixed overlay', async ({ studioDevtoolsPage }) => {
  const isVisible = await studioDevtoolsPage.isPanelVisible();
  expect(isVisible).toBe(true);
});
```

## Automation

### During `/cypilot-generate`

After completing implementation tasks, automatically:

1. Check if FEATURE.md contains UI requirements (keywords: "screen", "menu", "table", "button", "panel", "component")
2. If yes, run `/testing:spec-to-tests` with the FEATURE path
3. Mark testing tasks as completed after test generation

### Manual Override

Skip test generation with:
```markdown
<!-- SKIP_TEST_GENERATION: API-only change -->
```
in the FEATURE spec or phase plan.

## Validation

Before merging:

```bash
# Run generated tests
npx bddgen && npx playwright test --project=chromium

# Check coverage matches FEATURE spec
grep -n "Scenario:" src/mfe_packages/{mfeName}/tests/*.feature
```

All Actor Flows and Acceptance Criteria must have corresponding test scenarios.

